The Federal Government said it will support the use of locally made assistive devices for Persons With Disabilities (PWDs). It said the move would enable disabled persons live and make meaningful contributions to growth of the country. The Minister of Women Affairs and Social Development, Senator Aisha Alhassan made this known yesterday in Abuja at a stakeholdersâ€™ forum for local production of assistive devices for PWDs. She said the ministry would continue to encourage programmes aimed at improving the livelihood of PWDs with the limited resources available. Represented by the director, rehabilitation in the ministry, Victoria Akintaro, the minister said, the importance of assistive devices for the PWDs was to help facilitate mobility and improve their livelihoods. She added that the right of the devices for the PWDs is clearly stated in the United Nations Convention.